          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript is a treatise used for consultation by priests discussing the true nature of duty (Hindu law, Dharma) and contains different examples of daily rites to be performed by Hindus, including an emphasis on śrāddha rites (funeral rites). Manuscript includes some Vedic and non-Vedic rites as well as some devotional material (pūja).</summary>
            <textLang>In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Kṛtyatattva</title>
              <author>Raghunandana Bhaṭṭācārya, active 16th century</author>
              <colophon>Colophon: iti vandya [???] śrīhariharabhaṭṭācāryātmaja śrīraghūnandanabhaṭṭācāryaviracitaṃ kṛtyatattvaṃ samāptaṃ (f. 34).</colophon>
